commitResults.messageTitle: Add skeletal version of Project Portfolio Page (PPP)
commitResults.messageBody:
Created a skeletal version of joshua-tyh's Project Portfolio Page (PPP).

Project Portfolio Page (PPP) is to describe a member's contribution to
the project.

Only the headings and the phrase "to be added soon" were included in
this skeletal version.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add sort method in the Unique Person List class
commitResults.messageBody:
The implemented sort method sorts the list of persons based on their
delivery status. The setPersons method is then called to set the newly
sorted list.

Created the SortCommand.java that extends from Command and executes the
sort() method of the model.

The sort() method of model replaces the current list with a sorted list
based on delivery status in ascending order.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Sort Command to Address Book Parser
commitResults.messageBody:
The user is able to use the command word "sort" to execute the sort
feature.

Major bug detected:
After executing the sort command, the addressbook.json data file appears
to be wiped empty. Seems to be an issue with the logic of the
newly implemented sort() method. Requires immediate fixing.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix logic for sort() method in UniquePersonList
commitResults.messageBody:
The sort feature is now successfully implemented.

Fixed the bug where after executing the sort command, the address book
is wiped empty. Bug was cause by an unneccessary method call for
setPersons().

Codebase and DG touch ups for v1.3

Allowing for an email to be empty fixes the issue of previously being
unable to remove an email when editing.

Expected behaviour of the email field should follow that of an optional
field, in that it should be allowed to be empty within entries.

This fix will now allow users to input an empty string when editing the
email field.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update UG with fixed behaviour to remove optional fields.
commitResults.messageBody:
Explains how users can now safely remove the optional fields of phone
number and email address of a person.

This is a result of a bug fix to ensure the optional fields of phone
number and email address can hold blank fields.
